<!--                   Deterministic vs Stochastic -->
                  <section>
                    <section>
                        <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                        <h3 align='left'> Deterministic vs. Stochastic reactions </h3>
                        <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade"> 
                        <p style="font-size:30px" align='left'>
                        Consider ([A] & [B] constant): 
                          $$ A + B \overset{k_f}{\underset{k_b}\rightleftharpoons} C $$
                        </p>
                          
                        <p style="font-size:30px" align='left'>
                          <ul style="font-size:27px"> 
                            <li> Deterministic (macroscopic) &#8594 <b> Law of Mass Action (LMA): <br>
                            </b> Describes <b>concentration</b> with one ODE
                                $$ \frac{d[C]}{dt} = k_f[A][B] - k_b[C] $$ 
                                
                            </li>
                            <br>
                            <li> Stochastic &#8594 <b> Chemical Master Eq. (CME) </b> 
                                $$  \frac{dP_n(t)}{dt} = -(\lambda_n + \mu_n)P_n(t) +                                                
                        \mu_{n+1}P_{n+1}(t) + \lambda_{n-1}P_{n-1}(t) $$ 
                                - Describes <b>PDF</b> of <b>number of molecules</b> <br>
                                - Infinite ODE system for the probability distribution of the num. of molecules. <br>
                                - Trajectories solved by Gillespie or Tau-Leap algorithm
                            </li>
                          </ul>
                        

                    </section>
                    
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h3 align='left'> Deterministic vs. Stochastic reactions. </h3>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <p> LMA is a limiting case of CME: </p>
                        <img src="figsPG/CMELMAFPEshort.png" alt="CME Diagram">
                      <ul style="font-size:30px"> 
                        <li> The stochastic approach (CME) is more fundamental. </li> 
                        <li> Accounts for discrete probabilistic nature of chemical reactions </li> 
                      </p>
                      <div class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1" style="font-size: 35pt">
                      <div class="fragment highlight-red" data-fragment-index="1">
	                  <b> And difussion ...? </b>
	              </div>
	              </div>
                    </section>
                    
