<!--            Existing Models -->
                <section>
<!--                     Smoluchoskis model -->
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h3 align='left'> Diffusion Limited Reactions. </h3>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      
<!--                       Left column -->
                      <div style="float:left;width:60%;font-size: 25pt">
                         Chemical reactions controlled by diffusion <br></br>
                         <div class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1"> 
                          <p style="font-size:27px"> 
                              Consider: &nbsp $A + B \overset{k_S}\rightarrow C$ <br></br>
                              <ul style="font-size:27px">
<!--                                  <li> Very fast reactions (diffusion limited) </li><br>-->
                                  <li> Fixed spherical $A$ with Radius $R$. </li><br>
                                  <li> Initial uniformly distributed $B$'s around $A$. </li><br>
                                  <li> $B$'s undergo Brownian Motion &#8594 Diffusion $D$  </li><br>
                                  <li> If $B$ collides with $A$ &#8594 Reaction </li>
                              </ul>
                          </p>
                        </div>
                      </div>

<!--                       Right column -->
                      <div style="float:right;width:35%;">
                        <br></br>
                        <div class="fragment grow" data-fragment-index="1">
                            <img src="figsPG/difflimcartoon.png" width="350" >  
                        </div>
                        <div class="fragment" data-fragment-index="2" style="font-size: 30pt">
                          <div class="fragment highlight-red" data-fragment-index="2">
                            <br> </br>
                            <b> Reaction rate? </b>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </div>

                      <div style="clear: both;"></div>
                    </section>
                    
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h3 align='left'> Diffusion Limited Reactions. </h3>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      
<!--                       Left column -->
                      <div style="float:left;width:60%;">
                          <u> <b> Smoluchowski's model </u> </b> <br>
                              <ul style="font-size:27px">
                                  <li> $u(r,t):=$ concentration of $B$'s </li><br>
                                  <li> Model described by the PDE: 
                                  <p style="font-size:27px">
                                  $$  \frac{\partial u(r,t)}{\partial t} = \frac{D}{r^2}\frac{\partial}{\partial r}
                                  \left(r^2 \frac{\partial }{\partial r} u(r,t)\right) $$
                                  </p></li> <br>
                                  <li> Diffusion limited reaction
                                  <p style="font-size:27px">
                                  $$u(R,t) = 0 $$
                                  </p></li><br>
				                  <li class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1"> Reaction rate given by flux at $R$<br>
                                    $$k_S = 4\pi R D $$ </li>
                              </ul>
                          
                            <div style="font-size:27px">
                               
                            </div>
                      </div>

<!--                       Right column -->
                      <div style="float:right;width:39%;">
                          <div class="fragment grow" data-fragment-index="1">
                            <div class="fragment shrink" data-fragment-index="2">
                            <img src="figsPG/SmoluchowskiFull.png" width="280" >
                            </div>
                          </div>
                      <div class="fragment" data-fragment-index="2" style="font-size:25pt">
                        <div class="fragment highlight-red" data-fragment-index="2">
                        <b> Reversible? <br>
                          Stochastic process?</b>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                      </div>
                      <div style="clear: both;"></div>
                    </section>

                    
<!--                     REVERSIBLE REACTIONS -->
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h3 align='left'> Reversible reactions with diffusion</h3>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <p style="font-size:30px" align='left'> 
                      Consider: <span style="padding: 0 100px">&nbsp;</span> 
                       $ A + B \overset{k_f}{\underset{k_b}\rightleftharpoons} C $ <br> </br>
                      - Writing equation for PDF seems hard! <br> </br>
                      - Stochastic simulation using Brownian Motion, <br>
                      <ul>
                        <li> Where to put B after backward reaction? </li> <br>
                        <li> Too close will immediately react! </li> <br>
                      </ul>
                      </p>
                      <div class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1" style="font-size:34pt">
                       <div class="fragment highlight-red" data-fragment-index="1"> 
                        <b> Geminate recombinations! </b>
                       </div>
                      </div>
                    </section>
                    
<!--                     Kinetic Monte Carlo methods -->
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h4 align='left'> Kinetic Monte Carlo method for reversible reactions </h4>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <p style="font-size:30px" align='left'> 
                        - Our code to simulate reversible reactions. <br>
                      </p>
                      <!--                       Left column -->
                       <div style="float:left;width:48%;">
                      <p style="font-size:25px" align='left'>
                        For &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp $ A + B \overset{k_f}{\underset{k_b}\rightleftharpoons} C $ <br>
                      </p>
                      <ul style="font-size:25px" align='left'>
                        <li> Model Brownian motion with Random Walks for $A,B$ & $C$ in a box. </li>
                        <li> Diffusion limited forward reaction </li>
                        <li> Introduce an unbinding radius: place $B$ a distance $U_r$ after backward reaction. </li>
                        <li> Use Smoluchowski's model for each $A$ molecule, to adjust $U_r$ </li>
                        <li> <b> Note: </b> $U_r$ will depend on $A$ concentration $\Rightarrow$ Several iterations to find $U_r$ </li>
                      </ul>
                      </div>

<!--                       Right column -->
                      <div style="float:right;width:48%;">
                        <img src="figsPG/SimulationVis.gif" width="450" >
<!--                        <p style="font-size:23px" align='center' class="fragment grow" data-fragment-index="0">
                        - Only simulates trajectories. <br>
                        - Lacking rigorous mathematical/physical foundation.
                        </p>-->
                      <div class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1" style="font-size: 35pt">
                      <div class="fragment highlight-red" data-fragment-index="1">
                      <br> 
                      <b> Application? </b>
                      </div>
                      </div>
                      </div>
                      <div style="clear: both;"></div>
                    </section>
                    
                    <!--                 Applications to FCS -->                 
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h4 align='left'> Fluorescence correlation spectroscopy (FCS) </h4>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
<!--                       Left column -->
                      <div style="float:left;width:46%;">
                      <p style="font-size:23px" align="justify">
                        - FCS: experimental technique to measure <b>diffusion coefficients</b> and <b>reaction rates</b>. <br></br>
                        - Based on correlations of <b>linear</b> fluctuation around equilibrium.
                      </p>
                      <div class="fragment grow data-fragment-index="1">
                      <div class="fragment shrink data-fragment-index="2">
                        <img src="figsPG/FCSdiag.jpg" width="300" >
                      </div>
                        </div>
                      <p style="font-size:23px" align="justify">
                        - Fluctuations related to diffusion & reaction
                      </p>
                        <div class="fragment" data-fragment-index="1" style="font-size:23pt"> 
                        <div class="fragment highlight-red" data-fragment-index="1">
                        <b> KMC simulation rigorous? <br>
                            PDF instead of trajectories? </b>
                        </div> 
                        </div>      
                      </div>                

<!--                       Right column -->
                      <div style="float:right;width:46%;">
                        <img src="figsPG/FCS-correlationcurves.png" width="350" >
                        <p style="font-size:23px" align="left"> 
                          - Correlation curves match for linear reactions. <br></br>
                          - Slightly deviate for nonlinear reactions <br></br>
                          - They match in asymptotic cases: <br> nonlinear $\rightarrow$ linear 
                        </p>
                        
                      </div>

                      <div style="clear: both;"></div>

