<!--                 COUPLED DIFFUSION MODELS -->
                <section>
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h3 align='left'> Coupled diffusion model </h3>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <!--                       Left column -->
                      <div style="float:left;width:60%;">
			<ul style="font-size:23pt">
			  <li> Our model has a rigorous foundation: stochastic process corresponds to PDE. </li> <br>
			  <li> Only one $A$ fixed at the center and one $B$ with reversible reactions. </li> <br>
			  <li> Two random variables at time $t$: <br>
                  Continuous position X_t <br>
                  Discrete state $B_t=$ {Bound,Unbound} </li> <br>
			  <li> $f_u, f_b:$ probability distribution function (pdf) of unbound and bound $B$. </li><br>
			  <li> Generalizes easily to many B's </li> 
			</ul>
                      </div>
                      <!--                       Right column -->
                      <div style="float:right;width:40%;">
                         <br>
                         <div class="fragment grow" style="font-size:20pt">
                        <img src="figsPG/coupleddiffcartoon.png" width="700">
                        Stochastic process cartoon
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </section>
                    
                    <section>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <h3 align='left'> Coupled diffusion model </h3>
                      <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                      <p style="font-size:25px" align='left'> 
                      $$ \frac{\partial f_u(r,t)}{\partial t} = \frac{D_u}{r^2} \frac{\partial }{\partial r} \left( r^2 e^{-\beta U_u(r)} 
                         \frac{\partial}{\partial r} e^{\beta U_u(r)} f_A(r,t)\right) -\alpha(r)f_u(r,t) + \lambda(r)f_b(t)  \\
                         \frac{\partial f_b(r,t)}{\partial t} = \frac{D_b}{r^2} \frac{\partial }{\partial r} \left( r^2 e^{-\beta U_b(r)} 
                         \frac{\partial}{\partial r} e^{\beta U_b(r)} f_A(r,t)\right) + \alpha(r)f_u(r,t) - \lambda(r)f_b(t)  $$ <br>
                      <!--                       Left column -->
                      <div style="float:left;width:40%;">
			<img src="figsPG/CoupleDiff.png" width="400">
		      </div>
		      <!--                       Right column -->
                      <div style="float:right;width:60%;">
                        <br>
			<ul style="font-size:20pt">
                        <li>Using $\alpha(r)=\frac{k_0 \delta(r-R)}{4\pi r^2}$, $U_u=0$ and $\lambda(r)=0$  
                        $\Rightarrow$ Smoluchowski </li> <br>
                        <li> Using $\lambda(r)=\frac{k_1\delta(r-U_r)}{4\pi r^2}$ $\Rightarrow$ consistent with our KMC simulation. </li> <br>
                        <li> More general...? Numerical solutions for PDF? </li><br>
                       </ul>
                      </p>
                      </div>
		      <div style="clear: both;"></div>
                    </section>
                </section>      
                
