		<section>
                   <section>
                        <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                        <h3 align='left'> Motivation: traumatic brain injury (TBI) </h3>
                        <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
			<h6 align="left"> Collaborators at VA Hospital study mTBI in war veterans </h6>
			<p style="font-size:25pt"> <b>18% of combat veterans return with symptomatic mTBI </b></p> 
			<p style="font-size:20pt"> Exposed to 50-100 "mild" blasts </p> 

			  <!--                     LEFT COLUMN -->
			<div style="float:left;width:55%;font-size:30px;">  
			  <img src="figsPG/SB-tackle.jpg" width="550" >
			</div>
			    <!--                       Right Column     -->
			    <div style="float:right;width:45%;font-size:30px;">
			    <br>
			    <ul align="center">
			      <li> Blast waves (civilians too) <br></br> </li>
			      <li> Football players <br></br>
			      <li> Boxing <br></br> </li>
			      <li> Car/bike accidents </li> <br>
			    </ul>
			    </div>
			<div style="clear: both;"></div>
			<p style="font-size:25pt">
			Repetitive exposure to shocks in the head <!--set in motion pathogenic processes emerge-->
                          cause neurodegenerative disorders YEARS LATER!
                    </section>
                    
                     <section>
                        <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                        <h2 align='left'> Motivation </h2>
                        <hr align="left" width="900" size="5" noshade="noshade">
                        <p style="font-size:35px" align='left'>  
                        <b> We can help with computational experiments! </b> <br>
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size:30px" align='left'>
                          &nbsp &nbsp Our goal is to model of shock waves propagating through interfaces <br></br>
                            &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp - Air to skull and brain. <br>
                            &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp - Interfaces in experimental setups <br> </br>
                        </p>
                        <p style="font-size:35pt"> 
                        <b> Why are they useful?</b> <br>
                        </p>                        
                        <div class="fragment">
                        <p style="font-size:35px" align='left'>
                        <b> To bring insight into possible damaging mechanisms. </b> <br></br> 
                        </p>
			  <p style="font-size:28px" align='left'>  
			     &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp - Transmission and reflection through interfaces. <br>
			     &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp - Is the interface geometry relevant? <br> 
			     <!--&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp - Mechanotransduction at cell interface. <br> </br>-->
